dismissalText.commentary: Vaibhav Suryavanshi b Prasidh Krishna 101 (38b 7x4 11x6 59m) SR: 265.78

dismissalComment.html: It's over, but what a time he's given all of us tonight. Prasidh ends the hundred with a yorker that crashes into the stumps after Suryavanshi misses it. Jaiswal goes up to him and hugs him, the incoming batter Nitish Rana hugs him, so many GT players go up to him and congratulate him. This is one of the most incredible innings the IPL has ever seen in its 18 years, and it's been played by a 14 year old.
